Source: libusb-vhci
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Partizand <partizand@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 11)
Standards-Version: 4.1.3
Homepage: http://sourceforge.net/projects/usb-vhci/
#Vcs-Git: https://git.code.sf.net/p/usb-vhci/libusb_vhci

Package: libusb-vhci-dev
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: libusb-vhci (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Header files user-mode libraries for a virtual usb host controller.
 This project consists of a linux kernel driver and some user-mode libraries. They allow a process to create a virtual usb host controller. Real or virtual usb devices can be "plugged" into this controller. 
 https://sourceforge.net/p/usb-vhci/wiki/Home/

